---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="UtilHub privacy policy. We don't collect, store, or transmit your input data. Read the full policy here."
>
  <section class="container-narrow py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-50">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">
      Last updated: July 8, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none mt-8 dark:prose-invert">
      <p>
        <strong>Short version:</strong> UtilHub does not collect, store, transmit, or sell any of your
        input data. All tool processing happens locally in your browser.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        We collect almost nothing. Specifically:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No input data.</strong> When you paste text into a UtilHub tool, it never leaves your device. We do not log, store, or transmit it.</li>
        <li><strong>No personal information.</strong> We do not require accounts, email addresses, or names.</li>
        <li><strong>Standard server logs.</strong> Cloudflare Pages, our hosting provider, may log standard request metadata (IP address, user agent, requested URL). These logs are used solely for abuse prevention and operational debugging, are retained for a short period, and are not shared with us beyond aggregated counts.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
      <p>
        UtilHub sets <strong>one</strong> local-storage value: your theme preference (light or dark mode).
        We use no advertising cookies, no tracking cookies, and no third-party analytics scripts that store
        cross-site identifiers.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We may use privacy-friendly analytics (such as Plausible or self-hosted Umami) to understand aggregate
        traffic patterns. These tools do not use cookies and do not collect personal identifiers.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        UtilHub is free, and may display advertising through Google AdSense or similar programs once traffic
        thresholds are met. These ad networks use cookies to serve ads. You can opt out via
        <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads">Google Ad Settings</a> or
        <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info">DAA opt-out</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Children</h2>
      <p>
        UtilHub is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy occasionally. Material changes will be reflected in the "Last updated" date above.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions? Concerns? Visit our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
